Cleanups to switch kmalloc->kzalloc and to remove little redundant code found

ERROR:SPACING: space required before the open parenthesis '('
#85: FILE: drivers/char/tty_io.c:796:
+	if(test_bit(TTY_LDISC, &tty->flags)) {

Whitespace style used in the kernel sources is described in kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kmalloc(sizeof(*tp)...) over kmalloc(sizeof(struct ktermios)...)
#102: FILE: drivers/char/tty_io.c:1932:
+		tp = kmalloc(sizeof(struct ktermios), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

